      <hedline>
        <hl1>Global Warming's Effect</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>William B Shore letter holds that US should prepare for severe weather events caused by climate change and initiate steps necessary to reduce it</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Preparing for Nature's Attack'' (Op-Ed, April 1):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Preparing for Nature's Attack'' (Op-Ed, April 1):</p>
        <p>The United States should not only prepare for severe weather events caused by climate change; more urgently we should also initiate the many steps necessary to slow and eventually reduce climate change.</p>
        <p>A wide range of knowledge is required: a focus on scientific and technological research, a change in manufacturing and business practices, national land-use guidelines, an educational campaign for the public.</p>
        <p>We will need a road map to guide the myriad steps, and a clearer sense of priorities and mobilization of the resources required.</p>
        <p>Many universities, nonprofit organizations and businesses are taking steps -- but nowhere fast enough or comprehensively.</p>
        <p>William B. Shore  Sleepy Hollow, N.Y., April 1, 2006</p>
        <p>The writer is executive secretary of Nature Network and senior fellow of City University of New York's Institute for Urban Systems.</p>
      </block>
